headline: Intuit price target raised to $730 from $685 at Morgan Stanley
summary: Morgan Stanley raised the firm’s price target on Intuit (INTU) to $730 from $685 and keeps an Equal Weight rating on the shares. Overall revenues came in about 4% ahead of consensus, but 77% of the upside came from a sharp acceleration in Credit Karma, notes the analyst. Given a weaker than expected Q2 outlook and FY25 guidance that was left unchanged, “this debated stock likely remains debated,” the analyst tells investors. headline: Intuit price target raised to $640 from $600 at JPMorgan
summary: JPMorgan raised the firm’s price target on Intuit (INTU) to $640 from $600 and keeps a Neutral rating on the shares. The company’s fiscal Q1 results come in ahead of estimates, but Q2 total revenue and operating income were guided below the Street while the fiscal 2025 guidance framework is unchanged, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
